		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Using an american board with an american system will just avoid lockout cuip issues. Whether the game will run or not depends on how it was programmed.
<br />
<br />Probably very few games adjusted themselves automatically for PAL or NTSC systems, which means that most games will indeed run faster. The ones that rely on lots of Vblank time will probably have very corruped video. And the ones that rely on timed loops will probably have some visual glitches.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
